      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Ok Frodlin I see your point on the cannabalize spell being listed under the beneficial category. However going back to the description of the aa it specifies any spell that heals or harms,&amp;nbsp;and &amp;nbsp;debuffs under lucy are stated under the detrimental category. The word detrimental &amp;nbsp;is a synonym for harmful (which to me means debuffs should have always been included in gom). How are people supposed to know exactly what the devs wanted on this spell? I mean at the present time the aa still works&amp;nbsp;with the necro lich, which is also considered "beneficial". How do you justify it working with necro lich and not canny? I understand the reason for the change was to prevent gom procs from item procs and chain casting low or zero mana spells. Canny cannot be chain cast, only once every 18 seconds. No other class was near as affected as the shaman class with this change. Make it work with debuffs and hot's and I think the majority would be happy. If they are not going to adjust the aa and what can proc it they should allow for a refund since the aa has been altered and atm is significantly less useful to us now. As to the boohoo you guys are cursed with to much to do comment, why should we as a class be penalized because our primary role is not mainly damage or mainly healing? Sorry I know I am rambling but it is just disheartening to have something changed that affects&amp;nbsp;the class in such a negative way, have our community correspondent be told we where exploiting the whole time like a bunch of hackers, and then have to defend the reason we ask for a refund for the aa. Something should be done about it. Allow it to work with debuffs or hots or make canny cost 1 mana so it can once again proc gom. If neither of those are an option they should allow for a refund. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
